Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.87,0:01:39.54,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,How long until we arrive?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.33,0:01:42.33,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,We're almost at the Rialto Bridge. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rialto_Bridge}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.33,0:01:44.04,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,It will be another five minutes or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.04,0:01:46.09,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Good. Keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.09,0:01:49.42,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Buccellati, can you remind me \Nwhat the boss's orders entailed?{Literally "What were the contents of the order from the boss?" but that's daft. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.76,0:01:53.80,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I'll go over the boss's message again.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.35,0:01:59.14,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,{\an8}Listen closely. {I know this is insanely liberal but MEH -T}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.89,0:02:05.86,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,"The information contained on this disc was transferred to it \Nthe moment you all boarded the train in Naples.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.23,0:02:12.57,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,As such, I must inform you that I do not know\N if you are currently being pursued...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.57,0:02:16.74,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...nor how many of you have presently fallen.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.74,0:02:23.75,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The information on this disc will assist you in safely \Nreuniting me with my daughter, which is my final order.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.75,0:02:32.09,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,But I warn you; should you deviate from the instructions \Ncontained on this disc even slightly, you will be shown no mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.59,0:02:38.68,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,If any of you do anything I have not instructed, \Nwhether accidentally or intentionally...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.68,0:02:42.81,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...I will interpret it as an act of hostility.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.23,0:02:45.02,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Now, here is my final order.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.61,0:02:49.86,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Those of you remaining will depart...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.48,0:02:52.61,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...for the island of San Giorgio Maggiore. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_Giorgio_Maggiore}{I like how even Wikipedia mentions it being referenced in Jojo -T}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.61,0:02:57.53,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You will accompany my daughter to the top \Nof the great bell tower at the local church.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.07,0:03:02.70,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Once my daughter has been safely escorted there,\N your mission will be completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.08,0:03:06.12,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Order one: There are no stairs leading to the top of the tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.12,0:03:09.88,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Currently, the only means of reaching \Nthe top floor is through a single elevator.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.17,0:03:14.34,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Only Trish and one designated bodyguard \Nare permitted to use the elevator.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.34,0:03:21.06,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Order two: The bodyguard is prohibited from carrying any knives, guns, cell phones, or similar items.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.72,0:03:27.31,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,{\an8}Order three: You must reach the island \Nwithin fifteen minutes of successfully retrieving this disc.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.31,0:03:33.03,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,{\an8}Furthermore, the disc has been outfitted with a tracking device, \Nso I will know when you are on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.53,0:03:38.20,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Order four: The rest of you will remain on the boat. \NYou are not allowed to step foot on the island."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.49,0:03:39.41,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,That's everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.99,0:03:43.29,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Buccellati, we've arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.41,0:03:48.96,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,So the boss is at the top of that tower right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.96,0:03:52.04,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,He must be incredibly cautious\N considering how detailed his orders were.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.67,0:03:56.55,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Though I suppose if he weren't, \Nhe wouldn't be the boss of an organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.55,0:04:00.26,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Anyway, our mission is just about done now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.26,0:04:03.31,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,None of us died on the way, \Nso I guess it went well in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.31,0:04:06.68,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Yeah, just barely, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.68,0:04:09.48,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,We should have some fun in Venice\N for a bit before we head home.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.48,0:04:10.98,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I hear they got great eats.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.98,0:04:12.86,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,The food's good here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.86,0:04:15.82,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I forgot how hungry I was!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.82,0:04:17.95,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,What do they got?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.95,0:04:20.95,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Squid ink pasta, horsehair crab salad...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.95,0:04:25.45,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,...and I hear Hotel Cipriani serves great carpaccio. {https://www.belmond.com/hotels/europe/italy/venice/belmond-hotel-cipriani/}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.45,0:04:26.58,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Hey, knock it off!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.91,0:04:28.66,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Don't let your guard down!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.66,0:04:30.58,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,This mission isn't over yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.96,0:04:33.09,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Narancia, keep an eye on the radar.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.09,0:04:34.63,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,G-Got it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.92,0:04:36.42,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Buccellati...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.42,0:04:38.84,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...I volunteer to be her bodyguard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.30,0:04:43.30,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I'll escort her to the top of the bell tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.30,0:04:45.85,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Who the hell do you think you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.85,0:04:50.10,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,It's Buccellati's obligation as capo to escort her, idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.10,0:04:54.11,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,The boss didn't specify since\N he didn't know who would still be alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.03,0:04:59.36,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Of course. I'll go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.90,0:05:00.99,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,All right, Trish.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.32,0:05:04.37,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The two of us will enter the island as instructed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.67,0:05:15.09,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,I know...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.09,0:05:17.46,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,This is our chance to unmask the boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.46,0:05:19.09,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,I'll do whatever I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.67,0:05:25.30,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, Giorno. Could you give me that brooch of yours \Nas a good luck charm on this final mission?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.18,0:05:28.14,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Ladybugs are considered insects of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.60,0:05:30.43,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,They're symbols of life, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.14,0:05:33.23,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,They make good luck charms, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.52,0:05:35.23,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Oh, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.23,0:05:38.32,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Yes. Ladybugs bring very good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.16,0:05:48.45,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,This brooch imbued with life by \NGold Experience's ability will act as a tracking device.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.08,0:05:50.04,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Buccellati...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.91,0:05:52.58,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,What is it, Fugo?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.58,0:05:55.59,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,I would like to take this opportunity to say something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.59,0:05:57.55,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Why so formal? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.13,0:06:05.26,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,I believed you would become capo someday,\N and I believe you'll be able to complete this mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.35,0:06:07.47,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Of course he can.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.85,0:06:13.10,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Let's aim for an even higher position in the organization!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.77,0:06:17.11,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Yeah... We will.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.11,0:06:19.28,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Let's go, Trish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.90,0:06:27.07,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,If I can somehow get this onto the boss's body...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.07,0:06:29.37,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,...Giorno will be able to track him down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.00,0:06:33.71,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,For now, I need to figure out who he is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.04,0:06:35.21,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,...at any cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.05,0:07:30.35,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,The elevator is open.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.76,0:07:34.81,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,It only has buttons for the first floor and roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.81,0:07:37.19,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,It goes directly to either. \NThere are no other floors to stop on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.19,0:07:38.15,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,What's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.48,0:07:41.82,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,...What's going to happen to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.03,0:07:48.07,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,I was suddenly kidnapped by gangsters like you guys, \Nwas threatened with my life...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.07,0:07:53.16,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,...and now, I'm about to be taken\Nto a father I've never loved or even met.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.16,0:07:57.12,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,What will happen to me after this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.25,0:08:02.84,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The boss is just concerned for your safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.63,0:08:08.76,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,As for what will happen to you after this, \NI have a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.76,0:08:10.80,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,First, you'll be given a different name.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.68,0:08:14.14,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You may even need plastic surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.14,0:08:16.27,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You'll be given new ID and a new family registry...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.02,0:08:22.48,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...and be sent to some faraway country \Nwhere you'll live a happy life. {"faraway foreign" is redundant -G}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.15,0:08:26.53,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Your father has the power to make that happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.45,0:08:30.16,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Here. Let me give you a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.91,0:08:37.20,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,It's not as if... {I HATE TIMING LINES LIKE THIS AAAAAH -Gyro}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.87,0:08:41.21,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,...I-I'm nervous or anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.53,0:09:09.36,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,I wonder...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.28,0:09:12.82,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,...if I'll come to like my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.66,0:09:17.45,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,No family ever worries about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.87,0:09:22.46,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.46,0:09:23.75,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.21,0:09:28.09,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,To even worry about it is odd...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.67,0:09:31.30,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,We're almost at the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.14,0:09:39.85,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Trish? Tri{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.03,0:09:51.90,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Wh-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.11,0:09:56.28,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Trish... No... What's...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.41,0:10:00.70,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,Trish and I should be the only ones here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.70,0:10:04.79,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,No one other than the members of my team know I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.79,0:10:06.79,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,No... It couldn't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.79,0:10:08.71,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,Could the boss...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.71,0:10:11.26,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,...in order to ensure he remains hidden...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.26,0:10:14.22,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Did he give us this escort mission...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.76,0:10:20.60,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...so that he could personally eliminate his own daughter?!
Comment: 0,0:10:23.98,0:10:24.02,Main,,0,0,0,,B
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.36,0:10:35.20,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Bruno Buccellati was born the son of \Na fisherman in a suburb of Naples.{HOLY MOOD WHIPLASH, BATMAN. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.61,0:10:38.33,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,His father was never much of a people person...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.33,0:10:44.92,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...but he was an earnest and honest fisherman \Nwho tried to protect his family from the cruelties of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.83,0:10:47.88,Flashback,Bruno's Dad,0,0,0,,Bruno.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.88,0:10:48.79,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.46,0:10:51.26,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,You need me to fix the net?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.26,0:10:52.17,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.30,0:11:00.35,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,His mother was a kind woman, \Nand Buccellati loved the conversations he had with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.68,0:11:04.60,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,He eagerly looked forward to the\N bedtime stories she read him before he slept.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.60,0:11:06.85,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,All right, it's time to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.85,0:11:07.90,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.86,0:11:11.53,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Something happened when Buccellati was seven years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.53,0:11:13.94,Flashback,Bruno's Dad,0,0,0,,So what are you going to do about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.94,0:11:19.03,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,Well... I'm looking for change, \Nso I want to leave this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.91,0:11:23.25,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,After ten years of marriage, \Nhis parents divorced.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.83,0:11:28.96,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,As for why, only his parents could tell you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.29,0:11:32.42,Flashback,Bruno's Dad,0,0,0,,What are we going to do about Bruno?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.13,0:11:38.80,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,After talking it out among themselves, \NBuccellati's parents decided to let him decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.76,0:11:44.60,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,Bruno, your father and I both love you very much...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.60,0:11:46.60,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,...but we're going to be living apart from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.14,0:11:51.07,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,Who would you like to live with? \NMe or your father?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.07,0:11:53.03,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,We'd like you to decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.07,0:11:58.28,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,You want to leave this place \Nand go to the city with me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.28,0:12:00.41,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,You're a smart boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.41,0:12:02.49,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,You'd like to go to a good school, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.04,0:12:05.96,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,You'll meet so many more children your age there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.96,0:12:08.21,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,So you'll come live with me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.21,0:12:09.96,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,Won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.92,0:12:12.00,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.75,0:12:14.67,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,...want to live with Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.47,0:12:20.26,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,What?! \NBruno, you should really think about this!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.26,0:12:21.80,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,You like me better, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.64,0:12:25.18,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,I'm staying here with Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.18,0:12:26.60,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.27,0:12:30.15,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Mom is strong...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.15,0:12:32.23,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,She should be able to make it anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.23,0:12:33.23,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.49,0:12:39.99,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,All right, I'm leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.66,0:12:44.91,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,I'll come back once a month to visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.91,0:12:45.70,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.46,0:13:00.05,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,As Buccellati's gut feeling at the time warned him, \Nhis mother remarried to a man from Milan two years after leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.05,0:13:04.10,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,From then on, \Nhe only ever saw his mother at Christmas time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.10,0:13:11.69,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,His father, determined after his wife left him for the city, \Ndid his best to send Buccellati to a good school.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.69,0:13:15.07,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Dad, I think we'll get some customers soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.77,0:13:17.90,Flashback,Bruno's Dad,0,0,0,,Oh, I guess it's about that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.24,0:13:20.82,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,I'll reapply the nets.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.82,0:13:23.24,Flashback,Bruno's Dad,0,0,0,,All right. I'll let you handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.99,0:13:28.45,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Though he had been nothing more than a fisherman until this point, \Nin order to earn money for his son's tuition...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.45,0:13:34.21,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...he began taking tourists and other fishermen on his boat whenever he had time to spare.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.21,0:13:38.46,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,And the wheel of fate continued to turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.38,0:13:42.72,Flashback,Bruno's Dad,0,0,0,,Sirs, that island isn't good for fishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.72,0:13:44.39,Flashback,Bruno's Dad,0,0,0,,There are better{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.09,0:13:44.39,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,Whatever!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.39,0:13:46.89,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,That's where we wanna go fishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.89,0:13:49.39,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,So just shut up and take us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.39,0:13:50.60,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,We clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.48,0:13:54.31,Flashback,Bruno's Dad,0,0,0,,R-Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.11,0:14:01.90,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,That evening, Buccellati's father was rescued by the Coast Guard, \Nhis body riddled with bullet holes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.90,0:14:05.07,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,He's sustained seven bullet wounds to his arms, \Nshoulders, chest, and torso.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.07,0:14:06.70,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,Not all of the bullets passed through.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.99,0:14:04.24,Flashback,Nurse,0,0,0,,{\an8}We need an operating room open!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.24,0:14:06.70,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,{\an8}Dad! Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.70,0:14:08.95,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.50,0:14:15.75,Flashback,Nurse,0,0,0,,For now, please just wait until his surgery is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.75,0:14:19.71,Flashback,Nurse,0,0,0,,Be strong. \NDo you have contact information for anyone else in your family?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.71,0:14:20.80,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.76,0:14:28.68,Flashback,Cop,0,0,0,,Forensics is dropping by later, \Nso give them this as evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.68,0:14:29.64,Flashback,Nurse,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.64,0:14:30.47,Flashback,Cop,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.47,0:14:31.23,Flashback,Nurse,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.23,0:14:34.69,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,H-How did this happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.69,0:14:37.56,Flashback,Cop,0,0,0,,Evening, son.\N Is he your father?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.56,0:14:39.69,Flashback,Cop,0,0,0,,We found this at the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.32,0:14:44.45,Flashback,Cop,0,0,0,,Apparently, your father witnessed a drug deal going down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.45,0:14:46.53,Flashback,Cop,0,0,0,,They shot him up so he wouldn't speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.95,0:14:50.16,Flashback,Cop,0,0,0,,Your father is an important witness in this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.16,0:14:54.08,Flashback,Cop,0,0,0,,We'd rather he not die, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.08,0:14:55.71,Flashback,Cop,0,0,0,,{\an8}I'm sure he'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.08,0:14:57.50,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Dad was shot because of something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.67,0:15:04.43,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Luckily, Buccellati's father survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.80,0:15:09.14,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Despite being shot seven times, \Nnone of the wounds were fatal...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.51,0:15:13.73,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...and the boat that found and rescued him\N happened to have supplies to treat his wounds...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.73,0:15:16.19,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...which allowed him to survive \Nuntil he reached the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.19,0:15:18.61,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,He was graced by good luck all around.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.61,0:15:25.99,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,But in terms of Buccellati's life, \Nit may have been better if he had died.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.99,0:15:34.16,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,There are certain difficult situations\N where an opportunity to follow the right path isn't presented.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.04,0:15:42.88,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,Fishermen are way too damn tough, shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.88,0:15:45.34,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,I'll keep watch! \NJust hurry and finish him!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.34,0:15:48.26,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,You got a lot of nerve \Nmaking us come out here at night...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.26,0:15:50.93,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,Now go to hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.72,0:15:56.02,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,Wh-Who the fuck are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.02,0:15:59.02,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,A k-kid? H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.02,0:16:00.90,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,{\an8}What were you doing under the bed?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.90,0:16:02.98,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,{\an8}Th-That knife's dangerous! \NPut it down!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.11,0:16:02.98,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,It's just a fucking kid! \NGrab the knife!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.49,0:16:10.87,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,Wh-What are you{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.29,0:16:24.59,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,I'll protect you, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.96,0:16:29.13,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Don't worry. \NTake your time getting better.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.13,0:16:36.56,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,At the age of twelve, Bruno Buccellati committed murder \Nand entered a world no one should ever set foot in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.98,0:16:39.19,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,I can't turn back now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.19,0:16:42.19,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,They'll keep trying to get revenge and shut us up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.19,0:16:44.02,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,I can't trust the police, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.90,0:16:50.53,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,The only protection afforded to him and his father was \Nan organization that controlled the city from the shadows.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.86,0:16:53.45,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Buccellati knocked on the doors of that organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.20,0:16:58.04,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,And in return for his service and undying loyalty...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.04,0:17:00.50,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...they guaranteed his family's safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.50,0:17:05.21,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Believing the organization to be the true form of justice, he worked hard there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.21,0:17:10.38,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,He made a name for himself within the organization, \Nbefore the capo Polpo eventually took a liking to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.68,0:17:15.39,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Five years later, Buccellati's father died \Ndue to complications from his wounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.89,0:17:20.81,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Buccellati loathed the white powder of greed \Nthat had dragged him and his father into this situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.81,0:17:22.94,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...and swore that he would never forgive it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.48,0:17:24.36,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.82,0:17:28.65,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,I-I'm sorry!\N I won't bother them again!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.65,0:17:30.40,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,I'll forget about that family!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.40,0:17:34.66,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Good. \NNot like you'll be able to regret it once you're dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.66,0:17:36.41,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,If you're also a gangster{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.08,0:17:40.46,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Those are...!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.46,0:17:42.58,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Hey! \NWhat the hell is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.42,0:17:49.88,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,He learned that the organization's boss, a man whom he thought \Nembodied justice, was involved in dealing the drugs he despised.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.34,0:17:52.76,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,In this city?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.76,0:17:55.01,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,I thought they were forbidden!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.52,0:18:03.15,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,And now...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.15,0:18:04.52,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Now the boss is...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.02,0:18:07.11,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The most heinous form of evil...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.44,0:18:13.95,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...is to knowingly exploit the innocent for personal gain!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.95,0:18:17.12,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,A father did this to his innocent daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.12,0:18:18.95,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...all to cover his own ass?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.29,0:18:20.58,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Unforgivable!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.58,0:18:24.83,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Twice now you've betrayed my heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.13,0:18:33.93,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,There! \NTrish is still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.48,0:18:43.19,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,All right. It held.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.19,0:18:46.15,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,But damn, I can't see his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.44,0:18:51.57,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Boss, my original plan was just to uncover your identity,\N but things have changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.57,0:18:54.40,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I'm going to eliminate you here and now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.40,0:18:55.41,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I don't have time...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.70,0:18:58.66,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...but the boss won't be \Nexpecting me to betray him so suddenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.03,0:18:59.70,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,This will be...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.62,0:19:02.75,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...an assassination.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.67,0:19:09.21,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,I'll get ahead of the boss on \Nhis escape route and finish him there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.47,0:19:23.43,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,This...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.02,0:19:25.64,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,This hole...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.35,0:19:27.56,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.56,0:19:31.15,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,It's the stairway to the charnel house \Nlike you'd find in the basement of any church.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.48,0:19:35.90,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,Once he's eliminated Trish down there\N and thinks he's in the clear...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.90,0:19:38.91,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,...he'll make his escape \Nthrough the other side of the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.67,0:19:53.71,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,I managed to get here first.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.09,0:19:59.14,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,Here he comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.20,0:20:20.32,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,He came down the stairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.95,0:20:21.62,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.62,0:20:24.24,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,You would be wise to leave this place...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.24,0:20:25.54,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...Bruno Buccellati.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.62,0:20:28.87,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,If you step out from behind that pillar...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.87,0:20:31.08,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...you will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.30,0:20:39.76,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Sticky Fingers!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.64,0:20:46.35,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I-It's going to break off!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.61,0:21:00.49,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,So he knew I was after him...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.49,0:21:04.24,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,But since he hid himself again...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.24,0:21:06.87,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...I can only assume he isn't very powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.87,0:21:09.16,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I'd like to know your motive here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.79,0:21:13.96,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,What is the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.96,0:21:18.76,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I've had the utmost respect \Nfor your work on this mission thus far.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.38,0:21:22.59,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,{\pos(850,1055)}Did the joy of becoming a capo\N not satiate your greed?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.97,0:21:29.23,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,{\pos(850,1055)}Or has your hubris fooled you into believing you could get the better of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.89,0:21:32.19,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,When Trish wakes up...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.81,0:21:35.82,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...I'm going to tell her \Nthat she never had a father.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.82,0:21:37.15,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Trish?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.78,0:21:39.99,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,What about Trish?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.99,0:21:42.91,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,My daughter has nothing to do with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.91,0:21:46.87,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You'll never understand \Nwhat I feel within my heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.50,0:21:51.33,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Giorno?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.33,0:21:52.54,Narrator,Giorno,0,0,0,,Buccellati!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.54,0:21:55.50,Narrator,Giorno,0,0,0,,Yes, I know he's on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.50,0:21:59.17,Narrator,Giorno,0,0,0,,{\pos(1310,1055)}I know exactly where the brooch\Nyou put on the boss's body is.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.17,0:22:01.68,Narrator,Giorno,0,0,0,,{\pos(1310,1055)}Right now, he's at the bottom of the stairs\N leading to the charnel house.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.68,0:22:05.05,Narrator,Giorno,0,0,0,,He's right near the pillar that's \Nabout two meters away from the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.05,0:22:06.64,Narrator,Giorno,0,0,0,,But wait, Buccellati!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.89,0:22:09.93,Narrator,Giorno,0,0,0,,Something tells me... you're in trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.64,0:22:13.27,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,There you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.69,0:22:18.32,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Take this! \NSticky Fingers!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.49,0:22:28.74,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,The one who was in the pillar's shadow...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.20,0:22:30.25,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,...was me!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.58,0:22:36.92,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Wh-What...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.75,0:22:38.59,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,What's going o{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.59,0:22:42.63,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I've shown you this... as a parting gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.26,0:22:46.09,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Since this is the end,\N I'll enlighten you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.09,0:22:52.60,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,What you just saw and felt \Nwas yourself from the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.27,0:22:57.27,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,{\pos(1240,1055)}You from several seconds in the past\N just witnessed your future self.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.61,0:23:01.99,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,That is my King Crimson's ability. {Because of this line, I'm going to edit the rest as if it's Diavolo talking, not his Stand. -T}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.99,0:23:04.82,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,It erased time, then leapt past it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.57,0:23:09.70,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,No matter who dares try...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.70,0:23:15.29,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...I will not allow my \Nenduring dominance to be disrupted.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.79,0:23:18.59,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,{\an8}I must ensure that you disappear without a trace.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.09,0:23:25.68,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,{\an8}Buccellati, your mission to escort Trish...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.55,0:23:28.93,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...has come to an end.
